 the cause.";i:1;s:132:"If your garage door wont close one of the most common reasons is that the batteries in the remote have died and need to be replaced.";i:2;s:35:"To test if it is an issue with the.";i:3;s:299:"Garage Door will not close with wall button but closes with remote If your garage door will not close with the push button on the wall but your remote works fine you either have a faulty wall button or a wiring issue as the wall buttons are hardwired to the circuit board of your garage door opener.";i:4;s:90:"The sensors have small LED lights to let you know when the signal is on and uninterrupted.";i:5;s:83:"Thats very helpful in finding out if theyre the reason your garage door wont close.";i:6;s:138:"If the light is off the sensor itself is probably off and if the light is blinking it means something is getting in the way of the signal.";i:7;s:103:"If you are interested here are a few of the most common reasons why your garage door wont close at all.";i:8;s:54:"Your garage door remote batteries need to be replaced.";i:9;s:120:"One of the things you should definitely consider if your door wont close is to have your doors remote batteries changed.";i:10;s:76:"Your garage door remote is one of the means by which you can open your door.";i:11;s:60:"So if it does not have any battery left to power it up then.";i:12;s:108:"One of the most common reasons that the garage door may not close is because the lock-out button is engaged.";i:13;s:86:"This button is to prevent the door from opening or closing using the hand-held remote.";i:14;s:82:"To determine if this is the issue press the garage door button on the garage wall.";i:15;s:116:"You may need to adjust the limit screws if your garage door wont close all the way but will stop without retracting.";i:16;s:106:"Adjusting the contacts on these screws which tell the garage door opener how far to open or close is easy.";i:17;s:119:"Learn How to Organize a Shed Open the rear flap or remove the light cover on your garage door opener while up a ladder.";i:18;s:77:"Here are our recommendations for what to do when your garage door wont close.";i:19;s:96:"The first step to take when your garage door wont close is to look around and do a visual check.";i:20;s:72:"See if there is something under the door or blocking the safety sensors.";i:21;s:115:"If you notice that your garage door struggles to close on sunny days the sunlight is probably blinding the sensors.";i:22;s:71:"You can move your sensors out of the sunlight but this can be a hassle.";i:23;s:89:"This is especially true because the sun changes angles and directions throughout the day.";i:24;s:151:"If the issue is with the sensors youll likely find that you can use the garage door remote or wall-mounted switch to open the door but not to close it.";i:25;s:98:"Sometimes you can override this issue by holding down the switch until the door closes completely.";i:26;s:92:"If this works its another sign that the problem is due to a garage door safety sensor issue.";i:27;s:123:"One of the most common causes of a garage door that wont close during the wintertime is condensation on the safety sensors.";i:28;s:158:"If your garage door refuses to close when you push your remote control or the wired switch mounted to your wall your first check should be the safety sensors.";i:29;s:85:"These sensors mount on both sides of the door located a few inches above floor level.";i:30;s:97:"Limit switches look like two white knobs and you can usually find them on the garage door tracks.";i:31;s:83:"If the limit switches are not set properly your door wont open and close correctly.";i:32;s:67:"They can also interfere with the safety devices on the garage door.";i:33;s:60:"The best way to fix this issue is by adjusting the switches.";i:34;s:86:"If the garage door wont close try checking the wall station of the garage door opener.";i:35;s:96:"Using constant force press and hold the interior wall station until the door closes all the way.";i:36;s:80:"If this method solves the problem the issue must be in the garage doors sensors.";i:37;s:100:"If your garage door is still not closing you may want to check the batteries of your remote control.";i:38;s:76:"Replace them with fresh ones and try pushing the buttons to see if it works.";i:39;s:63:"There are some dust and dirt that built upon the roller tracks.";i:40;s:158:"Here are some of the most common reasons a garage door wont close all the way along with some simple DIY solutions you can use to get your door working again.";i:41;s:117:"Garage doors made after 1993 are equipped with safety sensors to prevent damage and injury while the door is closing.";i:42;s:43:"These sensors are valuable safety features.";}}